410 East 100th Street, south east corner of 1st Avenue, showing P. 99.
Board of Education, N.Y.C.
1920.

Riverside Park, at West 100th Street, showing the terrain to the south (No. 1) and to the north (No. 2)of this point.

Across the foreground are the New york Central Railroad tracks. Note the U. S. Training Ship "Illinois" anchored at 98th Street. This shortly will be moved to 135th Street.

On the Hudson River appear armed vessels of the U.S. Navy and small boats taking visitors to same.
The background is the New Jersey shore.

June 10, 1934
Views: 1-2
P.L.Sperr
